sec.p:
Descriptive terminology follows Konstantinov (1998). Holotypes of the new species are deposited in the
National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, DC, USA (USNM). Paratypes will be deposited in the
National Pusa Collection, Indian Agricultural Research Institute, New Delhi, India (NPC);
University of Agricultural Sciences, Bangalore, India (UASB);
Natural History Museum, London, United Kingdom (BMNH); and in the
personal collection of the first author (PKDC). Plant vouchers with accession numbers are deposited in the Calicut University Herbarium, Calicut, India. Different labels on specimens are denoted by numbers and separated by “;”.
